re shown to be not far from converged results of\nturbulent dissipation which allow us to obtain estimations of the Kolmogorov\nand Hinze scales. The computed Hinze scale is significantly larger than the\nsize of droplets observed and does not seem to be a relevant length scale to\ndescribe the smallest size of droplets formed in atomization.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Aug 2018 17:03:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-05"}
